# The ADR index is a hand-maintained table whose cells are dense with inline
# code spans. Prettier's markdown parser disagrees with GFM about where a code
# span ends when backticks sit adjacent to prose, and then "normalises" `_`↔`*`
# emphasis INSIDE what GFM renders as code — silently rewriting identifier names
# (`URL_KEYS`→`URL*KEYS`, `CHAIN_HREF_NAME_TAIL`, `server_name`). It does not
# converge either: successive runs flip the same tokens back and forth, so no
# amount of source rewording makes the file stable. A decision index that
# corrupts the constant names it cites is worse than an unformatted one, and the
# corruption lands on whichever commit happens to run `pnpm format` (ADR 1024/1025
# review finding — the defect predates that drain). Formatting is skipped here;
# keep rows hand-wrapped.
docs/adr/README.md
